com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.consumer

Class PostHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.consumer.PostHandler

  • public class PostHandler
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the post handler for the UPA consumer application. It provides methods for sending on stream and off stream post messages.

      • handlePosts

        public int handlePosts(ChannelSession chnl,
                       com.thomsonreuters.upa.transport.Error error)
        Uses the current time and the nextPostTime to determine whether a postMsg should be sent. If a post message should be sent, the time is calculated for the next post after this one. Additionally, the postWithMsg flag is toggled so that posting alternates between posting with a full message as payload or data as payload.
